Demonstration of point-to-point communication.

This time though, instead of sending simply an integer, we're sending a string.

Note that we can safely print the received message immediately after the call
to `MPI_Recv`, and that, again, is because it is a blocking receive operation,
meaning it stops the program execution at that point until it fully receives
the data, and only then proceeds with the rest of the program. Therefore, by
the time we get to the point where we call the `printf` function, the data is
completely received, placed in the `msg` buffer, and it is safe to read the
values in the receive buffer.
